  "body": "> /kind bug\r\n\r\n**What happened**:\r\nWhen we delete a device plugin, its exported resources are still listed in node status.\r\n\r\n**What you expected to happen**:\r\nThe resource should be removed after its device plugin is deleted.\r\n\r\n**How to reproduce it (as minimally and precisely as possible)**:\r\nThe existing test/e2e/scheduling/nvidia-gpus.go has already been extended to reproduce this bug.\r\n\r\n**Anything else we need to know?**:\r\n\r\n**Environment**:\r\n- Kubernetes version (use `kubectl version`): 1.8\r\n- Cloud provider or hardware configuration**:\r\n- OS (e.g. from /etc/os-release):\r\n- Kernel (e.g. `uname -a`):\r\n- Install tools:\r\n- Others:\r\n",
